Note that this character is replaced in modern Japanese by the simplified character {{term|lang=ja|湾|tr=wan}}, rather than the simplified Chinese character {{term|lang=cmn|弯|tr=wān||bend, curve}}.  The Japanese simplified version means {{term|lang=en|bay}} or {{term|lang=en|inlet}} when used on its own, but now also includes the {{term|lang=en|bend}}, {{term|lang=en|curve}} meanings when used in compounds.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

